            <fr:title text="A finite sequence of simple extensions is a finitely generated extension">A finite sequence of simple extensions is a finitely generated extension</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be an extension, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r}\in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>. Define the extensions
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}=F_{0}\subseteq  F_{1}\subseteq …\subseteq  F_{r}]]></fr:tex>
by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{i+1}=F_{i}(\alpha _{i+1})]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{r}=\mathbb {F}(\alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r})]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p><fr:link href="/nst-002K/" title="Proof by induction" uri="http://localhost:8000/nst-002K/" display-uri="nst-002K" type="local">Proof by induction</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
<html:p><html:strong>Base case</html:strong>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r=1]]></fr:tex>. The result is immediate.</html:p>
<html:p><html:strong>Inductive case:</html:strong> For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex>, suppose the result <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{r}=\mathbb {F}(\alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r})]]></fr:tex>. We want to prove the claim for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r+1]]></fr:tex>, i.e.,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r})(\alpha _{r+1})=\mathbb {F}(\alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r},\alpha _{r+1}).]]></fr:tex>
But this is literally the base case.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
