            <fr:title text="Jordan–Hölder theorem">Jordan–Hölder theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gr-000G/" title="Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-000G/" display-uri="gr-000G" type="local">Group</fr:link>. If
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {1}_{G}=H_{0}\mathrel {\triangleleft } H_{1}\mathrel {\triangleleft }…\mathrel {\triangleleft } H_{n}=G,]]></fr:tex>
and
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {1}_{G}=K_{0}\mathrel {\triangleleft } K_{1}\mathrel {\triangleleft }…\mathrel {\triangleleft } K_{m}=G,]]></fr:tex>
are two <fr:link href="/gr-003X/" title="Composition Series" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-003X/" display-uri="gr-003X" type="local">Composition Series</fr:link>s for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m=n]]></fr:tex> and there exists a permutation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi \in  S_{n}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H_{j+1} / H_{j}\cong  K_{\sigma (j) + 1} / K_{\sigma (j)}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:p>In other words, the <fr:link href="/gr-003X/" title="Composition Series" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-003X/" display-uri="gr-003X" type="local">Composition Series</fr:link> for a group is unique.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p><fr:link href="/nst-002K/" title="Proof by induction" uri="http://localhost:8000/nst-002K/" display-uri="nst-002K" type="local">Proof by induction</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\min (m,n)]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
<html:p><html:strong>Base case:</html:strong> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\min (m,n)=1]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/gr-003W/" title="Simple" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-003W/" display-uri="gr-003W" type="local">Simple</fr:link>, hence any other composition series is of length 1 and the unique subquotient is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
<html:p><html:strong>Inductive argument:</html:strong> This is rather lengthy, I'll return to it.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
